## 2. Industrial automation engineer with field commissioning

**What it is:** These engineers program PLCs (Siemens Step7, TIA Portal, Rockwell), design SCADA systems, and develop HMI interfaces — but critically, they also travel to factories, power plants, and processing facilities to commission and troubleshoot the physical systems they've programmed. The role is roughly 50% office-based software development and 50% on-site in steel mills, cement plants, or bottling lines.

**Why AI can't replace it:** Every industrial installation is different. Commissioning a rolling mill automation system requires crawling through machinery, debugging sensor wiring, recalibrating actuators, and adapting code on the fly when physical reality doesn't match the schematic. This hands-on troubleshooting in hazardous, variable industrial environments is precisely what AI cannot do.

**Romanian market reality:** This is the **highest-volume hybrid niche in Romania**, with **800+ listings on Hipo.ro** and **1,088 on Glassdoor**. Specific postings include SMS Metallurgy Romania (software developer + worldwide commissioning, €1,245–€1,650/month entry-level), IMSAT SA (5+ years experience, Siemens/Rockwell, national/international projects), Teamland (robotics automation, **8,000–10,000 RON net/month = ~€1,800–€2,200 net**), and Varta Microbattery in Brașov. Senior automation engineers at Continental, Bosch, or Siemens Romania earn **€2,500–€4,000/month gross** easily. The role benefits from Romania's massive automotive manufacturing base — Continental alone operates in Timișoara, Sibiu, Brașov, Iași, Bucharest, and Arad.

**Where to find postings:** Hipo.ro (search "automatizări" or "automation engineer"), BestJobs.eu, Glassdoor Romania, LinkedIn. Companies: Continental, Bosch, Siemens, Honeywell, IMSAT, Contec, Smartech Automation.

