## 3. CSRD sustainability consultant — EU regulation creates a gold rush

**What it is:** The EU's Corporate Sustainability Reporting Directive (CSRD) requires thousands of companies to report on **80+ disclosure requirements and 1,100+ data points** covering carbon emissions, biodiversity impact, supply chain labor practices, and more. CSRD consultants conduct physical environmental audits and site assessments, then translate findings into compliant digital reports using ESRS standards, GHG accounting frameworks, and EU Taxonomy classification.

**Why AI can't replace it:** The role demands on-site facility inspections, stakeholder interviews, double materiality assessments involving qualitative judgment, and navigation of complex, evolving regulatory frameworks. Romania implemented OMF 85/2024 aligning with EU CSRD, and phased obligations from 2024–2028 guarantee **years of sustained demand** before the market matures.

**Romanian market reality:** **EY denkstatt Romania** is described as the "largest provider of sustainability consulting in Romania" and actively hires ESG consultants. Other firms include **Accace Romania**, **Stratos Romania**, and **ECONOS**. Salaries for mid-level ESG consultants range from **€2,000–€4,500/month**, with the sweet spot at €2,500–€3,000 for 2–4 years of experience. Remote opportunities abound — **Watershed Technology** (London/Paris/Berlin + remote Europe) and **ADEC Innovation** both hire remote sustainability specialists across the EU.

**Where to find postings:** LinkedIn (search "CSRD" or "ESG consultant Romania"), Indeed remote (136+ sustainability Europe remote jobs), Jobgether (5,474 remote sustainability listings), Glassdoor.

