## 4. Renewable energy O&M and commissioning engineer

**What it is:** Operations & Maintenance engineers for solar and wind installations combine hands-on electrical work — climbing wind turbines, troubleshooting inverters on solar farms, managing high-voltage systems — with digital monitoring through SCADA platforms, performance analytics dashboards, and predictive maintenance algorithms.

**Why AI can't replace it:** Wind turbines break in storms. Solar panel arrays develop faults in remote fields. These problems require a human to drive to a rural site, climb infrastructure, diagnose physical failures, and repair them — while simultaneously understanding the digital monitoring systems that flagged the issue. Romania's geography (Dobrogea for wind, southern plains for solar) means many installations are far from urban centers.

**Romanian market reality:** Romania has **4.2 GW of new solar/wind capacity** awarded through its CfD scheme, €415 million from the Modernization Fund for clean energy, and **1,168 energy jobs open on Glassdoor Romania**. Key employers include **Enery Romania** (solar/wind parks in Cluj, Constanța, Tulcea), **Nofar Energy** (€192M EBRD financing, 531 MW solar), **Monsson Group** (building a 1,044 MW solar park in Arad — one of Europe's largest, €800M investment), and **Rezolv Energy** (Vifor wind farm). Renewable energy engineers in Bucharest average **~€2,395/month gross** (SalaryExpert). SCADA/automation specialists in the energy sector command similar or higher pay.

**Where to find postings:** Glassdoor Romania (search "solar engineer," "wind energy," "SCADA energy"), LinkedIn, BestJobs.eu. Companies: Enery, Simtel Team, Nofar Energy, Monsson, Hidroelectrica.

